This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama commemorating the 150th anniversary of the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA). The proclamation highlights the history and achievements of the USDA, including its efforts during the Great Depression, World Wars, and in areas such as soil conservation, nutrition assistance, food safety regulations, and environmental protection. The USDA continues to serve the public interest by providing leadership on agriculture, natural resources, safe and nutritious food, research, and related issues. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe May 15, 2012, as the 150th Anniversary of the USDA and honor its contributions to the welfare of the nation.